post_cb({"bq_ids": {"n4140": {"so_10187283_10187622_0": {"length": 10, "quality": 0.9090909090909091, "section_id": 1766}}, "n3337": {"so_10187283_10187622_0": {"length": 10, "quality": 0.9090909090909091, "section_id": 1760}}, "n4659": {"so_10187283_10187622_0": {"length": 10, "quality": 0.9090909090909091, "section_id": 1936}}}, "12746286": {"Id": "12746286", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>There's a minor bug. There might be no input available. You're not checking the return value of <code>getline(cin,text);</code>. This is unlikely to happen; you'd need to have e.g. input redirection and an empty input file.</p>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2012-10-05T12:29:18.003", "CommentCount": "0", "CreationDate": "2012-10-05T12:29:18.003", "ParentId": "10187283", "Score": "0", "OwnerUserId": "15416"}, "10187622": {"Id": "10187622", "PostTypeId": "2", "Body": "<p>The person who asked the question might have thought that the <code>pos</code> argument to <code>find</code> needs to be in the range <code>[0, length)</code>. This is not the case however, from the standard 21.3.6.3/2:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p id=\"so_10187283_10187622_0\">Returns: xpos if the function can determine such a value for xpos.\n  Otherwise, returns npos.</p>\n</blockquote>\n", "LastActivityDate": "2012-04-17T08:20:55.663", "CommentCount": "2", "CreationDate": "2012-04-17T08:20:55.663", "ParentId": "10187283", "Score": "3", "OwnerUserId": "125672"}, "10187283": {"ViewCount": "120", "Body": "<p>here is  short fragment of code,which test if there is any spaces in given string</p>\n<pre><code>#include&lt;string&gt;\n#include&lt;iostream&gt;\n#include&lt;cctype&gt;\nusing namespace std;\n//performs string operations\nvoid string_get()\n{\n    string text;\n    cout&lt;&lt;\" enter string \"&lt;&lt;endl;\n    getline(cin,text);\n    string::size_type position=text.find(' ');\n    if(position!=string::npos)\n    {\n        if(text.find(' ',position+1)!=string::npos)\n        {\n            cout&lt;&lt;\" contains at least two spaces \"&lt;&lt;endl;\n\n        }\n        else\n        {\n            cout&lt;&lt;\" contains less then two spaces \"&lt;&lt;endl;\n\n        }\n            }\n\n\n    else\n    {\n\n        cout&lt;&lt;\" no spaces \"&lt;&lt;endl;\n    }\n\n    }\n\nint main()\n{\n\n    string_get();\n\n\n\n    return 0;\n}\n</code></pre>\n<p>when i run  this code and enter some string,it works fine,but there is such question,namely it says that there is bug in this code and i am asked to fix it,but i could not see which bug is here?maybe string is NULL?or string does not contain any spaces?which case i have to consider?</p>\n", "AcceptedAnswerId": "10187622", "Title": "which bug is in following code?", "CreationDate": "2012-04-17T07:54:53.983", "Id": "10187283", "CommentCount": "8", "FavoriteCount": "1", "PostTypeId": "1", "LastEditDate": "2012-04-17T08:02:34.097", "LastEditorUserId": "516138", "LastActivityDate": "2012-10-05T12:29:18.003", "Score": "-1", "OwnerUserId": "466534", "Tags": "<c++><string>", "AnswerCount": "2"}});